<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="115" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Diagnostic description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
Entirely dark brown to black, except by paired pink vittae on pronotal disc (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Costalampys joanae sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Sternum IX, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view, blue arrow pointing to the transverse keel on the dorsal plate; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view; L, Aedeagus, oblique view, red arrow pointing to the ventral plate. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-C); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (D-L)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543219" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">16A</figureCitation>
), as about as long as 1/2
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
disc length, as wide as 1/3
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
disc width. Elytron (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Costalampys joanae sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Sternum IX, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view, blue arrow pointing to the transverse keel on the dorsal plate; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view; L, Aedeagus, oblique view, red arrow pointing to the ventral plate. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-C); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (D-L)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543219" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">16A</figureCitation>
) dark brown to black, without any pale-yellow longitudinal stripe. Legs (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Costalampys joanae sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Sternum IX, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view, blue arrow pointing to the transverse keel on the dorsal plate; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view; L, Aedeagus, oblique view, red arrow pointing to the ventral plate. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-C); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (D-L)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543219" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">16B</figureCitation>
) dark brown to black. Sternum VIII entirely dark brown, without lateral vitreous spots. Pygidium (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Costalampys joanae sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Sternum IX, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view, blue arrow pointing to the transverse keel on the dorsal plate; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view; L, Aedeagus, oblique view, red arrow pointing to the ventral plate. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-C); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (D-L)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543219" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">16F</figureCitation>
) entirely dark brown.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543219" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" start="Figure 16" startId="F16">
