<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
Pronotum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Costalampys joanae sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Sternum IX, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view, blue arrow pointing to the transverse keel on the dorsal plate; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view; L, Aedeagus, oblique view, red arrow pointing to the ventral plate. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-C); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (D-L)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543219" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">16D</figureCitation>
) with sides rounded, divergent posteriorly. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Male.</emphasis>
Total length = 10.6 mm; Pronotal length = 2.2 mm; Pronotal width = 3.6 mm; Elytral length = 8.4 mm; Elytral width = 2.3 mm. Antennomere III (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Costalampys joanae sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Sternum IX, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view, blue arrow pointing to the transverse keel on the dorsal plate; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view; L, Aedeagus, oblique view, red arrow pointing to the ventral plate. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-C); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (D-L)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543219" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">16C</figureCitation>
) with lamella about 4
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than core antennomere. Sternum VI (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Costalampys joanae sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Sternum IX, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view, blue arrow pointing to the transverse keel on the dorsal plate; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view; L, Aedeagus, oblique view, red arrow pointing to the ventral plate. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-C); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (D-L)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543219" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">16B</figureCitation>
) with a small lantern, occupying the medial 1/6 of the sternum, not reaching its anterior margin. Sternum VIII (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Costalampys joanae sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Sternum IX, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view, blue arrow pointing to the transverse keel on the dorsal plate; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view; L, Aedeagus, oblique view, red arrow pointing to the ventral plate. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-C); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (D-L)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543219" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">16E</figureCitation>
) with posterior margin bisinuose. Pygidium (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Costalampys joanae sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Sternum IX, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view, blue arrow pointing to the transverse keel on the dorsal plate; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view; L, Aedeagus, oblique view, red arrow pointing to the ventral plate. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-C); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (D-L)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543219" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">16F</figureCitation>
) with sides rounded and abruptly converging posteriorly from basal third on, posterior corners barely visible, posterior margin rounded, somewhat acuminate. Syntergite (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Costalampys joanae sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Sternum IX, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view, blue arrow pointing to the transverse keel on the dorsal plate; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view; L, Aedeagus, oblique view, red arrow pointing to the ventral plate. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-C); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (D-L)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543219" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">16G,H</figureCitation>
) boomerang-shaped (with anterior margin strongly curved). Phallus (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Costalampys joanae sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Sternum IX, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view, blue arrow pointing to the transverse keel on the dorsal plate; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view; L, Aedeagus, oblique view, red arrow pointing to the ventral plate. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-C); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (D-L)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543219" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">16I-L</figureCitation>
) with dorsal plate curved dorsally in lateral view, with sides rounded at apical half, slightly convergent apically. Paramere apex almost straight, ventral projection (lateral view) moderately developed, almost right-angled. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="115" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
<taxonomicName authority="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" authorityName="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Costalampys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Costalampys joanae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="joanae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Costalampys joanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">sp. nov.</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. delicata" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="delicata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">C. delicata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">sp. nov.</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. decorata" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="decorata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">C. decorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Olivier, 1888) 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">comb. nov.</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. tricolor" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="tricolor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">C. tricolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Gorham, 1880) 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">comb. nov.</emphasis>
, and 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. bella" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="bella">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">C. bella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">sp. nov.</emphasis>
, in the dorsal color pattern (overall brown or dark brown, with pronotal disc broadly pink, and with an elongate pale-yellow spot on elytron). 
<taxonomicName authority="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" authorityName="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Costalampys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Costalampys joanae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="joanae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Costalampys joanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">sp. nov.</emphasis>
is unique among the aforementioned species by having a longer antennomere III lamella, which is about 4
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than core antennomere, as well as sides of pygidium strongly convergent posteriorly (homogeneously rounded in the other species).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
